</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="127" pageNumber="836" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="127.[1482,2688,1752,2685]" pageId="127" pageNumber="836">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1484,1832,2416,2449]" pageId="127" pageNumber="836">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Near Threatened on The IUCN Red List. No data are available on population trends. Major threats include large-scale loss of primary forest habitat. Small patchy distribution (not much larger than 20,000 km?) and restricted habitat have generated concern over conservation of Swynnerton’s Bush Squirrel.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
